               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440701-name-416" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440701-name-416" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440701-name-416" type="surname" value="FOX"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440701-name-416" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK FOX</persName>
                  </hi>. I am assistant to John Hardman Pickford—he has one partner—on the 26th of June, I had a waistcoat inside the door—I missed it—I went after the prisoner, and caught her forty or fifty yards from the door—I told her she had a waistcoat—she gave it to me—this is it—it was con<lb></lb>cealed under the child which she was carrying.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> She said she had picked it up, and a boy dropped it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I saw the lining hang down beneath the child.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How long was it after you had seen it safe? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About five minutes—I did not see anybody else about.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
